[32m│[0m - NULL: Likely treated as missing/empty field                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Empty array: PHP may reject array-to-string comparison                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Security implications:**                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This vulnerability demonstrates why **strict comparison (`===`)** should     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m always be used for security-sensitive operations in PHP. The loose           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m comparison operator can lead to authentication bypasses through type         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m manipulation.                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Next steps for remediation:**                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Replace `==` with `===` in password validation                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Implement proper session management (not serialized cookies)               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Add type checking before comparisons                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Use password hashing with `password_verify()` which does strict comparison [32m│[0m
